cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE, cs.CR 

This paper focuses on evaluating the ability of graph neural networks to perform logical generalization, which is a key topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses neural networks, which suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with benchmarking and evaluation, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
